gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nets 124, Magic 104
gameRecap.excerpt: The Nets defeated the Magic, 124-104. Spencer Dinwiddie led all scorers with 29 points, along with nine assists for the Nets, while Mikal Bridges added 21 points, four assists and four steals in the victory. Franz Wagner tallied 21 points and eight rebounds for the Magic in the losing effort. The Nets improve to 2-1 in East Group C play, 6-5 in the regular season, while the Magic fall to 0-1 in East Group C play, 5-5 in the regular season.
